  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Mix together curry powder, salt, and thyme in a small bowl.",
    "In a large skillet, heat coconut oil over medium heat. Add garlic and ginger and sauté for 1 minute.",
    "Add chopped fernbrake-gosari, curry powder mixture, and chopped Scotch Bonnet peppers. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Add crumbled bread, coconut milk, and lime juice. Stir to combine.",
    "Transfer mixture to a 9x13 inch baking dish and bake for 25 minutes.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with thyme sprigs.",
    "Refrigerate leftovers for up to 3 days.",
    "Reheat in oven at 350°F (180°C) for 10-15 minutes before serving."
